    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today with a high-ceiling core anchored by **Tyler Soderstrom** (76.91) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21). Both benefit from high-efficiency matchups against Michael Wacha and Luis Severino respectively; in both cases, park factors and SP skill metrics provide a significant tailwind that lifts their base projections into our elite tier. **Corbin Carroll** remains a critical engine for our SB-starved squad, carrying a strong 75.04 score; despite facing a modest arm in Sproat, his combination of batting order security and dynamic platoon metrics makes him an automatic start. **Josh Naylor** rounds out our top-tier plays (72.22), as he remains locked into the cleanup spot against Taj Bradley, effectively insulating his production from the volatility of the lower order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Alex Freeland**, who hovered just shy of our start threshold with a 49.05 efficiency score. While he presents a solid floor, the optimizer prioritized the specific situational advantages of **Brice Turang** and **Kyle Karros**, both of whom cleared the 60-point barrier thanks to favorable park factors and high-impact platoon matchups. Notably, we have opted to sit **Austin Riley** (43.75) and **Jose Caballero** (39.32) today; the former struggles against the elite profile of Skubal, while the latter fails to meet our 40-point floor due to a brutal combination of a tough matchup against Eovaldi and an unfavorable batting position. \n\nWe are monitoring the status of **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Tyler Soderstrom**, both of whom are currently listed as \"Lineup Pending.\" Should either be scratched, we will look to rotate in **Alex Freeland** or **Travis Bazzana** to maintain our game cap efficiency. Additionally, while **Trevor Story** (59.77) technically lands just below our \"Strong\" tier, his elite BvP history against Lauer serves as an internal tie-breaker that justifies his inclusion over lower-upside bench options. With the wind blowing out in the game featuring **Kyle Karros** and **Mickey Moniak**, we are positioned to capitalize on high-scoring potential despite the latter's platoon disadvantage.",
